Galumna (Galumna) mikoi sp. n. is morphologically most similar to Galumna (Galumna) innexa Perez-Inigo & Baggio, 1986 from the Neotropical region (see
Perez-Inigo and Baggio 1986
) in having striate pteromorphs, minute interlamellar setae, anterior notogastral margin, four pairs of rounded porose areas on notogaster and median pore. However, the new species differs from the latter by the foveolate notogaster and anogenital region (vs. not foveolate in Galumna (Galumna) innexa ), striate posterior part of notogaster (vs. not striate in Galumna (Galumna) innexa ) and clavate bothridial setae (vs. lanceolate in Galumna (Galumna) innexa ).
